			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The x86-64 validator currently allows REX prefixes with bits set that do not affect the prefixed instruction.  For example, all of the following instructions are accepted when only the first would be generated by an assembler:

  83 c0 01                add    $0x1,%eax
  40 83 c0 01             rex add    $0x1,%eax
  44 83 c0 01             rex.R add    $0x1,%eax

Since the other instructions will never be generated by an assembler, they will rarely be tested, so there is a slight chance that CPUs might have bugs and handle these incorrectly.
